            <p style="font-family:cursive ;font-size: larger;"><b>My family has been making this apple pie recipe for generations, and it never fails to please.</b></p>
        </section>
        <section class="ingredients">
            <h2 style="font-family: cursive;color:blueviolet;">INGREDIENTS</h2>
            <ol>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">1/2 cup sugar</li>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">2 tsp ground cinnamon</li>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">5 medium-sized apples, peeled and sliced</li>
                
            </ol>
        </section>
        <section class="instructions">
            <h2 style="font-family: cursive;color:blueviolet;">INSTRUCTIONS</h2>
            <ol>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).</li>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">In a bowl, mix the sugar and cinnamon.</li>
                <li style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;font-size: large;">Toss the apples in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.</li>
                
            </ol>
        </section>
    </main>
